<TITLE> Police seize Buddha statue in Old Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com)Police Monday seized a touchstone statue of Buddha from a hotel on Nawabpur Road in Old Dhaka, a Sutrapur police officer said. Sub-inspector Anwar Hossain of Sutrapur Police Station told bdnews24.com that police had raided Nidu Hotel, acting on a tip-off, and retrieved the 2.37kg statue around 11.30am. Hossain said Gopal Chandra Roy, a gold merchant certified by Bangladesh Bank, confirmed that the statue is up to 800-year-old. Roy put the market value of the eight-inch tall statue at Tk 2.5 crore, the police officer said. No arrest was made. The sub-inspector said the police quizzed hotel employees and checked information about boarders. Police said one of the boarders might have brought the statue to hotel and left it there for fears of arrest by law enforcers. bdnew
